    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AudioManager
    manages all the audio of the game.
    BoBo
     
    BoboView
     
    Card
    card interactable object used to access Computer object.
    CardView
    view of the Card used to access the computer.
    Computer
    computer interactable object model used to control the enemies (Drone, Dog in the room, just like in the original impossible mission.
    ComputerCard
    model of the computer card, just a placeholder, so that can easily check if this item is in invenotry to acces the Computer
    ComputerCardView
     
    ComputerView
    view of the Computer interactable object
    Dog
    model of the dog Entity, it extends the Entity abstract class.
    DogView
    view counterpart of the Dog model.
    Drone
    model of the 'drone' enemy, extends the Entity abstract class.
    DroneView
    view counterpart of the Drone model.
    EnemyView
    view, it contains all the views of all enemies in the Player's current Room.
    Entity
    model, abstract class of a game entity.
    GameController
    controller component, updates all the entities states, and requests the game view to render.
    GameController.GameState
    state of the game.
    GameKeyListener
     
    GameView
    view, this is the components that requests each view's draw() method.
    InputHandler
    controller, handles keyboard input processing for the Player and menu navigation.
    InteractableObject
    abstract class, model, interactable objects such as chests, computers(to disable the enemies), etc...
    InteractableObjectsView
    view , every single interactable object views is collected in here.
    Inventory
    model of player's inventory.
    InventoryView
     
    Item
    model, abstract class of an 'Item' that can be collected and put in the Player 's Inventory
    ItemView
     
    Ladder
    ladder model, it is considered an InteractableObject so that it is easier to implement in the .txt based level editor.
    LadderView
    view of the Ladder model
    Leaderboard
    model, represents the 'leaderboard' object.
    Leaderboard.LeaderboardEntry
    represents a leaderboard entry for when a player successfully extracts.
    LeaderboardView
    view, renders all the leaderboard rankings and points data provided by the Leaderboard model.
    LeaderboardViewController
    controller of the LeaderboardView view and Leaderboard model.
    LevelManager
    model, the class initializes the game world / tutorial layout in the LevelManager.worldLayout matrix.
    LevelView
    view, handles the rendering of the level's tiles and tutorial text.
    Main
     
    MetalLocker
    metal locker interactable model.
    MetalLockerView
    view of the MetalLocker model
    PaperBox
    paper box interactable object model.
    PaperBoxView
    view of the PaperBox model
    PauseMenuController
    controller of the pause menu, helps to process the pause menu navigation and coordinates the TitleScreenView and GameView.
    PauseMenuView
    view, renders the pause menu.
    Player
    player model, handles everything that a player does: movement, object interaction, computer screen navigation.
    PlayerView
    view of the Player model.
    PokerCard
    model of a single 'poker card' item.
    PokerCardsView
     
    PokerCardView
     
    RedBox
    red box interactable object model.
    RedBoxView
    view of the RedBox model
    ResultScreenController
    controller of the result screen, handles enter key processing that allows the user to go back into the title screen.
    ResultScreenView
    view of the result screen, renders the result screen based on the Player's ScoreTracker.
    Room
    model, contains an inner enum Room.RoomType,s contain utility methods, primarily a class that allows working on enemies in the room.
    Room.RoomType
    describes the type of the room
    ScoreTracker
    'observer' of the 'Player model, tracks the number of InteractableObject opened, provides card sequence checkers and has various computing utility methods to get the total points.
    ScreenSettings
    !VERY! important model, only contains field regarding the game screen size.
    Tile
    model, stores tile data : it is kept simple because the heavy work is done in TileManager.
    TileManager
    model, initializes all the various tiles information in the TileManager.tiles array.
    TitleScreenController
    controller of the TitleScreenView, game entry point.
    TitleScreenView
    view of the title screen, handles the rendering/logic of the title screen.
    WhatsYourNameController
    controller of the WhatsYourNameView view.
    WhatsYourNameView
    view that user sees when he presses the 'new game' in the title screen.
    WoodLocker
    wood locker interactable object model.
    WoodLockerView
    view of the WoodLocker model
